Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
lineSelect(25.10)                                            lineSelect(25.10)

Name
       lineSelect  -  Selects  all objects that fall across the specified line
       coordinates

Syntax
       lineSelect

       [-help]

       <mode>

       <ux1><uy1><ux2><uy2>

       Selects all objects that fall across the  specified  line  coordinates.
       The lineSelect command is equivalent to the Select by Line check box in
       the Selection page of the Preferences form.

       Innovus  provides  an easy way to toggle between window and line selec-
       tion modes using the GUI:

              * The default selection mode is window.

              * Press the Ctrl key to switch to the line selection mode.  With
                the  Ctrl key pressed, draw a line across the objects you want
                to select. All the objects that the line crosses are selected.

              * When you release the Ctrl key,  the  selection  mode  switches
                back to window.

       Note: This command works only in GUI mode.

Parameters
       -help  Prints a brief description that includes type and default infor-
              mation for each lineSelect parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man lineSelect

       <mode> Specifies  the  action  to  be  performed on the objects falling
              across the specified line coordinates. Choose one of the follow-
              ing modes:

              * new: Selects all objects crossed by the  line.  This  mode  is
                equivalent  to  the  Select by Line check box in the Selection
                page of the Preferences form.

              * delete: Deletes all object selections crossed by the line. Use
                this mode if multiple objects are selected and you want to de-
                select some of them but retain the other selections.

              * append: Selects objects crossed by the line and  appends  them
                to the current selection.

              * toggle:  Deselects objects in the bounding box if they are se-
                lected; selects objects if they are deselected.

       <ux1 uy1 ux2 uy2>
              Specifies the start and end points of the line.

Example
       The following command selects all objects falling across the  specified
       line coordinates.

       lineSelect new 168.654 994.049 688.129 436.224

